description:
After an incredible 88 years of life, Ellen White passed away in 1915. Co-founder of the Seventh Adventist Church, she travelled across the globe, living all over the United States of America, in Australia and spent time in Europe, too. She is the most translated American author and the third most translated author of all time. She lived a full life with her legacy long  continued after her death, still recognised today. She has inspired education, health work, publishing, and missions all over the world.

To find out more information about Ellen Whites Death visit our website to read our extended article.
